<item>
            <title>[LU-11959] Improve handling of &apos;network&apos; client mount option</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11959</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &apos;network&apos; client mount option enables to limit connections from the client to be on the specified network NID.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the moment, connection to the MGS is out of the scope of this option, which lets a Lustre client use a different LNet network for the mgc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And when used in a routed environment, the network specified as a restriction has to be the one defined on server side, which is conflicting with the definition given for the &apos;network&apos; option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will push patches to address these two points.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
